From: Yang Wei <Wei.Yang@windriver.com>
Date: Tue, 13 May 2014 10:21:31 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] usb/dwc2: Fix a build error

After enabling PCI, there is a build error.

error: implicit declaration of function 'devm_ioremap_resource'
[-Werror=implicit-function-declaration]

Signed-off-by: Yang Wei <Wei.Yang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/usb/dwc2/pci.c |    6 +++---
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/dwc2/pci.c b/drivers/usb/dwc2/pci.c
index 3d14c88..d131a1b 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/dwc2/pci.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/dwc2/pci.c
@@ -129,9 +129,9 @@ static int dwc2_driver_probe(struct pci_dev *dev,
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
 	hsotg->dev = &dev->dev;
-	hsotg->regs = devm_ioremap_resource(&dev->dev, &dev->resource[0]);
-	if (IS_ERR(hsotg->regs))
-		return PTR_ERR(hsotg->regs);
+	hsotg->regs = devm_request_and_ioremap(&dev->dev, &dev->resource[0]);
+	if (!hsotg->regs)
+		return -EADDRNOTAVAIL;
 
 	dev_dbg(&dev->dev, "mapped PA %08lx to VA %p\n",
 		(unsigned long)pci_resource_start(dev, 0), hsotg->regs);
